    "body": "following up on https://github.com/neovim/neovim.github.io/pull/454\r\n\r\n- Took me a bit of time because I wanted to start from an empty config (not necessarily minimal) that we could possibly reuse to update screenshots https://github.com/teto/home/tree/noctalia/config/nvim-neovim.io\r\n- images width is sometimes too big. Codex advised me a piece of code but I would rather have someone knowledgeable with hugo/webdesign advice\r\n- I haven't asked permission to share neovide screenshots.  project is MIT, should be fine ?\r\n\r\nI initially envisioned the \"screenshots\" page as \"what is possible\" since I remember  when I started using vim: what's the appeal it's so dry ! While I believe vim distributions to be misallocated efforts, their screenshots showed me vim could be made much sexier.\r\n\r\nYou mentioned showcasing features @justinmk so I added things I thought were visual and relatively new.\r\n\r\nLet me know what you think.",
    "closed_at": "2026-05-06T10:02:30Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "You could use the [figure shortcode](https://gohugo.io/shortcodes/figure/) to configure image width. \r\n\r\nInstead of placing the images globally in `./static` you may also use a [page bundle](https://gohugo.io/content-management/page-bundles/) (but not a blocker, just neat) ",
